{"id":9148,"date":"2025-12-05T19:48:26","date_gmt":"2025-12-05T16:48:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/emuseum.torus.kz\/exhibit\/68da7c8058f44f19f-en\/"},"modified":"2025-12-31T12:57:36","modified_gmt":"2025-12-31T09:57:36","slug":"68da7c8058f44f19f-en","status":"publish","type":"exhibit","link":"https:\/\/e-museum.kz\/en\/exhibit\/68da7c8058f44f19f-en\/","title":{"rendered":"Knife with Sheath"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Knife with Sheath\u2014a skillfully crafted national item that combines practical use with decorative value. The knife has a total length of 25 cm, featuring a sharp, single-edged blade forged from durable white metal. The tang and handle are made from a single piece of wood, covered on the outside with white metal. The handle surface is decorated with intricate twisted patterns created using an engraving technique, adding artistic beauty to the piece. Additionally, the handle is fitted with a round white metal ring that serves both decorative and reinforcing purposes.Sheath\u2014made entirely of white metal, with the interior lined with wood to securely hold the blade. The sheath measures 19 cm in length and features carved patterns spaced 9 cm apart. It is covered on both sides with fabric trimmed with red fur, enhancing its ornamental appeal. The sheath is decorated with small convex studs and equipped with a loop for attaching it to a belt, making it both practical and elegant for everyday use.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":0,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"","ast-site-content-layout":"default","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","ast-disable-related-posts":"",